print("\n=== 4. Universality — constructing ALL quantum-logical systems ===")
print("""The set {H, T, CNOT} (all built from primitive folds) is universal:
• Any single-qubit unitary (any local fold/twist) is generated densely by H and T.
• CNOT provides entanglement (non-local tunneling).
By the Solovay-Kitaev theorem, repeated combinations of these gates can approximate
ANY unitary U ∈ SU(2^N) to arbitrary precision ε.
Therefore every possible consistent network of distinctions — i.e., every quantum-
